{
  "texts": [
    "Embedding layerIn natural language processing (NLP), the word embedding approach is used to represent words as numerical vectors.",
    "This is accomplished by giving each word in a corpus (collection of text) a vector with a fixed size.",
    "These vectors are usually generated using a neural network-based method, where the network is trained on huge amount of text data and the word vectors are learned by optimizing a specific objective function.",
    "The generated vectors store various aspects of each word's meaning, including its context, grammar, and semantics.The ability to manipulate words mathematically by performing operations like vector addition and subtraction on them makes it feasible to gain insightful knowledge about the relationships between words.",
    "In several NLP tasks, such as sentiment analysis, named entity recognition, and machine translation, word embeddings have shown to be tremendously helpful."
  ]
}